---
// Legacy URL structure was `/content/<pub>/<slug>`; the redesign
// flattens to `/<pub>/<slug>`. Rather than remap each old slug (rkeys
// differ between the old GH-CMS and the current PDS), send all stray
// `/content/...` URLs to the all-content index — readers land
// somewhere coherent instead of a 404, and can navigate from there.
//
// This is a rest-param route instead of a config `redirects` entry on
// purpose: rest params rank below static segments in Astro's route
// priority, so `/content` (index) and `/content/page/N` (deep
// pagination) win, while everything else under `/content/` falls
// through to here. The old `/content/[publication]/[slug]` config
// redirect matched `/content/page/2` and shadowed pagination.
export const prerender = false;

return Astro.redirect("/content", 301);
---
